[[fi:VHDL-kieli FPGA-suunnittelussa/4-bittinen BCD-laskuri]]
{{FULLBOOKNAME}}{{FULLBOOKNAME}}{{FULLBOOKNAME}}

That's the Greek letter Sigma. It means 'sum of', so Kirchoff's First Law is stating that the sum of all the currents going into a point equals the sum of all the currents leaving the point. So:

I<sub>in<sub>1</sub></sub> + I<sub>in<sub>2</sub></sub> + I<sub>in<sub>3</sub></sub> + ... + I<sub>in<sub>n-2</sub></sub> + I<sub>in<sub>n-1</sub></sub> + I<sub>in<sub>n</sub></sub> = I<sub>out<sub>1</sub></sub> + I<sub>out<sub>2</sub></sub> + I<sub>out<sub>3</sub></sub> + ... + I<sub>out<sub>n-2</sub></sub> + I<sub>out<sub>n-1</sub></sub> + I<sub>out<sub>n</sub></sub>

